text: Meteli () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Metelinsky Selsoviet, Duvansky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 1,080 as of 2010. There are 10 streets. == Geography == It is located 75 km from Mesyagutovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Duvansky District
title: Meteli
